  38:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** /**
  39:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @defgroup FIR Finite Impulse Response (FIR) Filters
  40:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  41:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   This set of functions implements Finite Impulse Response (FIR) filters
  42:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   for Q7, Q15, Q31, and floating-point data types.  Fast versions of Q15 and Q31 are also provided.
  43:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   The functions operate on blocks of input and output data and each call to the function processes
  44:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <code>blockSize</code> samples through the filter.  <code>pSrc</code> and
  45:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <code>pDst</code> points to input and output arrays containing <code>blockSize</code> values.
  46:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  47:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par           Algorithm
  48:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The FIR filter algorithm is based upon a sequence of multiply-accumulate (MAC) o
  49:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Each filter coefficient <code>b[n]</code> is multiplied by a state variable whic
  50:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <pre>
  51:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       y[n] = b[0] * x[n] + b[1] * x[n-1] + b[2] * x[n-2] + ...+ b[numTaps-1] * x[n-numTaps+1]
  52:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   </pre>
  53:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  54:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    \image html FIR.GIF "Finite Impulse Response filter"
  55:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  56:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    <code>pCoeffs</code> points to a coefficient array of size <code>numTaps</code>.
  57:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Coefficients are stored in time reversed order.
  58:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  59:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <pre>
  60:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       {b[numTaps-1], b[numTaps-2], b[N-2], ..., b[1], b[0]}
  61:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   </pre>
  62:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  63:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    <code>pState</code> points to a state array of size <code>numTaps + blockSize - 
  64:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Samples in the state buffer are stored in the following order.
  65:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  66:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <pre>
  67:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       {x[n-numTaps+1], x[n-numTaps], x[n-numTaps-1], x[n-numTaps-2]....x[n](==pSrc[0]), x[n+1](==pS
  68:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   </pre>
  69:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  70:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  71:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Note that the length of the state buffer exceeds the length of the coefficient a
  72:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The increased state buffer length allows circular addressing, which is tradition
  73:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    to be avoided and yields a significant speed improvement.
  74:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The state variables are updated after each block of data is processed; the coeff
  75:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  76:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par           Instance Structure
  77:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The coefficients and state variables for a filter are stored together in an inst
  78:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    A separate instance structure must be defined for each filter.
  79:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Coefficient arrays may be shared among several instances while state variable ar
  80:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    There are separate instance structure declarations for each of the 4 supported d
  81:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  82:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par           Initialization Functions
  83:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    There is also an associated initialization function for each data type.
  84:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The initialization function performs the following operations:
  85:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    - Sets the values of the internal structure fields.
  86:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    - Zeros out the values in the state buffer.
  87:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    To do this manually without calling the init function, assign the follow subfiel
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccI1heDP.s 			page 3


  88:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    numTaps, pCoeffs, pState. Also set all of the values in pState to zero.
  89:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
  90:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
  91:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Use of the initialization function is optional.
  92:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    However, if the initialization function is used, then the instance structure can
  93:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    To place an instance structure into a const data section, the instance structure
  94:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Set the values in the state buffer to zeros before static initialization.
  95:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    The code below statically initializes each of the 6 different data type filter i
  96:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   <pre>
  97:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_f64 S = {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
  98:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_f32 S = {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
  99:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_f16 S = {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
 100:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_q31 S = {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
 101:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_q15 S = {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
 102:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****       arm_fir_instance_q7 S =  {numTaps, pState, pCoeffs};
 103:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   </pre>
 104:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    where <code>numTaps</code> is the number of filter coefficients in the filter; <
 105:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    <code>pCoeffs</code> is the address of the coefficient buffer.
 106:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 107:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par          Initialization of Helium version
 108:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  For Helium version the array of coefficients must be padded with zero to contain
 109:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  a full number of lanes.
 110:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 111:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  The array length L must be a multiple of x. L = x * a :
 112:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - x is 4  for f32
 113:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - x is 4  for q31
 114:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - x is 4  for f16 (so managed like the f32 version and not like the q15 one)
 115:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - x is 8  for q15
 116:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - x is 16 for q7
 117:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 118:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  The additional coefficients 
 119:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  (x * a - numTaps) must be set to 0.
 120:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  numTaps is still set to its right value in the init function. It means that
 121:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  the implementation may require to read more coefficients due to the vectorization 
 122:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  to avoid having to manage too many different cases in the code.
 123:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 124:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par          Helium state buffer
 125:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  The state buffer must contain some additional temporary data
 126:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  used during the computation but which is not the state of the FIR.
 127:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  The first A samples are temporary data.
 128:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  The remaining samples are the state of the FIR filter.
 129:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 130:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par
 131:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  So the state buffer has size <code> numTaps + A + blockSize - 1 </code> :
 132:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - A is blockSize for f32
 133:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - A is 8*ceil(blockSize/8) for f16
 134:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - A is 8*ceil(blockSize/4) for q31
 135:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                  - A is 0 for other datatypes (q15 and q7)
 136:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 137:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****   @par           Fixed-Point Behavior
 138:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Care must be taken when using the fixed-point versions of the FIR filter functio
 139:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    In particular, the overflow and saturation behavior of the accumulator used in e
 140:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****                    Refer to the function specific documentation below for usage guidelines.
 141:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 142:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c ****  */
 143:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** 
 144:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/FilteringFunctions/arm_fir_f32.c **** /**
